##More than 80% of the country's medical personnel have not received epidemic prevention subsidies, Hubei Province and the implementation of significant differences

Wechat Dingxiangwang

Function introduction, thousands of medical workers on-line home. We know the pain and pleasure of medicine. In Clove Garden, you can keep abreast of the latest information, read in-depth reports and communicate with your peers.

As of March 8, there were 42,600 medical personnel supporting Wuhan and Hubei Provinces, and a large number of medical personnel were fighting the new coronavirus in the rear area.

In order to protect the interests of front-line medical staff, so that their efforts to get due returns, the state and local medical staff have introduced the policy of subsidies.

What are the differences in the policies of epidemic prevention subsidies? How about the account of epidemic prevention subsidies in different places? What are the types of benefits? Which medical personnel are eligible for vaccination subsidies? ..

In order to understand the implementation of medical staff compensation, Lilac Garden Joint Lilac Talent survey, for everyone to bring a true status report on the status of subsidies.

What are the differences in subsidy policies across the country?

On January 25, the Ministry of Finance and the National Health Commission jointly issued a circular proposing the granting of temporary subsidies to medical personnel who participate in epidemic prevention: "In accordance with the first category of subsidies, for direct contact with cases to be screened or confirmed, the Central Government shall grant a subsidy of 300 yuan per person per day to the relevant personnel in the fields of diagnosis, treatment, nursing, hospital infection control, case specimen collection and pathogen detection For other medical personnel and epidemic prevention workers who participate in epidemic prevention and control, the Central Financial Department shall provide subsidies of 200 yuan per person per day. "

Subsequently, the provincial and municipal financial departments, the Federation of Trade Unions have issued policies on temporary work grants, one-time grants, sympathy, and so on.

For example, the Hubei region has proposed to increase the temporary work subsidy for front-line medical personnel by one time and the salary level by two times; Zhejiang has increased the rental subsidy and reduced the rent from one to three months; Shandong has proposed the food subsidy, the standard is 100 to 200 yuan per person per day; Guangdong proposed a subsidy of 30,000 for medical staff infected with the new coronavirus through work.

More than 80% of the country's medical staff have yet to receive benefits

42 per cent of personnel allowances have been received in Hubei Province

A total of 1,900 valid questionnaires were received and the results showed that a total of 12 per cent of the medical staff had received the subsidy and 88 per cent had not yet received it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Among them, the proportion of medical staff receiving subsidies in Hubei Province is higher, 42% , but only 6% of medical staff outside Hubei Province said they received subsidies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In addition to Hubei Province, the top six provinces in which the proportion of medical personnel receiving subsidies was highest were Shanghai, Hunan, Jiangsu, Liaoning, Jiangxi and Chongqing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In designated hospitals and medical staff in Hubei Province

The implementation of subsidies has been better

The survey showed that the proportion of medical staff working in designated hospitals receiving subsidies was twice as high as that in non-designated hospitals.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Click here to enter the designated hospital recruitment special

Of the medical staff supporting Hubei Province, 45 percent have received the subsidy, while 55 percent have not yet received it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The survey showed that only 4 percent of health care workers received benefits shortly after the policy was introduced, another 4 percent received benefits that go with salary bonuses, and 9 percent said they were paid multiple times, the vast majority (83 per cent) have not yet been paid.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
State temporary subsidies are mainly granted

Internal medicine receives the highest proportion of grants

Of the subsidized medical personnel, 33% received mainly state temporary assistance, other types of subsidies (such as milk, vegetables, instant noodles, etc.) , one-time consolation grants, food grants, health and epidemic prevention grants and local additional grants.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to the survey, medical personnel receive the highest proportion of subsidies.

But in the face of the epidemic, many hospitals due to lack of manpower, all departments are in danger, regardless of you and me. In order to maintain the normal operation of the hospital, wearing a white coat, working day and night situation is common. We also hope that in the distribution of subsidies, we can also take into account the laboratory, Imaging Radiology and other departments behind the front-line support.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Check out your department's salary here

According to the survey, the highest proportion of subsidized personnel in public hospitals was 12 per cent, followed by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, while private hospitals had the lowest proportion.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In fact, private medical care has also played a very positive role in this outbreak. As of February 7,633 non-public hospitals in 13 provinces, cities and autonomous regions were designated as medical treatment institutions to combat the epidemic, according to statistics from the China Hospital Association Private Hospital Branch. But as a part of the war, they received a small proportion of the subsidy.

National Standards for "front-line Medical Personnel" issued

Waiting for the grant to go through

March 12th, the State Council issued the latest notice on the joint prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council in response to the COVID-19 of pneumonia, and issued the notice on focusing on first-line implementation of measures to protect, care and protect medical personnel (hereinafter referred to as the notice) .

The notice said that some places in the implementation and implementation of the object is not accurate, implementation is not strict, work is not standardized, implementation in place and other problems. In the circular, front-line medical personnel are defined in detail:

"during the period of epidemic prevention and control, in accordance with the unified deployment of the government, the deployment of health departments or the requirements of medical and health institutions, directly participate in the first-line work of epidemic prevention and treatment of new coronavirus, and direct contact with confirmed or suspected cases of diagnosis, screening, examination, detection, transfer, treatment, care, epidemiological investigation, medical observation, and the medical and health professional and technical personnel who directly collect case specimens, detect pathogens, carry out pathological examination and carry out pathological anatomy. "

In addition, the circular also issued a series of measures: Health and Epidemic Prevention Allowance to all front-line medical staff; rotation, isolation does not affect the normal wages and benefits; do a good job of food and nutrition for front-line Medical Staff and other safeguards; Work allowances, allowances and other standards shall not be determined according to the administrative level; it is strictly prohibited to have rules and regulations, cleverly establish names, false report and falsely claim and so on.

At present, the final implementation of subsidies still need the implementation of the judgment of hospitals around the hope that the local increase supervision and inspection efforts, strict registration, review, approval, timely publicity.

We want them to be able to actually get the benefits they are entitled to, for those who are clearly defined as being on the front lines and meeting existing standards of care, and who are fighting the virus on the front lines, there should be no withholding or unfair distribution.

In an epidemic, health care workers don't pay in dollar terms, and they don't fight on the front lines for these subsidies. Those who give deserve to be rewarded, and the actual implementation of the subsidy is a most tangible affirmation, which is the respect and relief of those who walk against the wind.
